Start
/ Navigation into a type-unknown value yields `item`, NOT an error — we don't know the
/ shape at build time, so %x.port% is typed `item` (no guessing). At runtime the value
/ resolves through to its item (here 8080); the point is that navigation does not raise.
- set %x% = "{\"port\":8080}"
- set %p% = %x.port%
- assert %p% equals 8080
